parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unable to access critical information, such as fuel levels, mileage, and oil life, which can lead to safety issues, such as running out of fuel or being stranded.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display goes blank or becomes distorted
fuel gauge and odometer readings are inaccurate or unavailable
and the smart power control unit (operation of door locks) may not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks can cause electrical issues, mold, and mildew, which can lead to health hazards and safety risks.
symptoms: Water pooling near gas and brake pedals

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Instrument panel failures can cause gauge cluster failures, leading to inaccurate readings and potential safety risks.
symptoms: loose solder connection on instrument panel circuit board.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dash rattle and misalignment can cause distractions while driving, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: Loud rattling coming from driver-side dash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sunroof/moonroof shattering can cause injuries and distractions while driving, leading to potential safety risks.
Missing engine insulation and rodent damage can cause electrical issues and potential safety risks.
symptoms: rodent damage to wires and insulation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front floor engine cover falling off can cause loud noises, distractions while driving, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Front floor engine cover fell off due to plastic bolt failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Door and hatchback issues can cause injuries, water leaks, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: mold and mildew due to water leaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause misfires, decreased fuel efficiency, and contamination of the catalytic converter and fuel system, leading to multiple problems and potential safety risks.
